    <h1 class="page-title">about</h1>
    <p class="page-standfirst">product leader, builder, and new yorker working on enterprise ai adoption.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="content-stack reveal">
    <p>i'm a product leader, fourteen years in, currently director of product management at salesforce on the emerging technology team. my work is enterprise ai adoption: the gap between what a model can do and what a large organization will actually absorb. that gap is where the hard, interesting problems live.</p>
    <p>before salesforce, it was siriusxm, disney+, and ea. streaming and connected-car platforms, a global launch across sixty-plus markets, a zero-to-one sports app that grew into a real product. the numbers are on the work page.</p>
    <p>what's different now is that i build, not just spec. i run a small fleet of ai systems on a mac mini in my apartment: an agent that handles my operational layer, an eval runner that keeps me honest about which model to use, a cost router that cut my spend without cutting capability. some of it ships. some of it doesn't survive contact with reality. i write about both.</p>
    <p>based in new york city.</p>
  </div>

